      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'How much fiber do kids need daily?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'The American Academy of Pediatrics recommends children consume their age plus 5 grams of fiber daily (the "age plus 5" rule). For example, a 6-year-old needs approximately 11 grams per day. The Institute of Medicine provides more specific guidelines: children ages 1 to 3 need 19 grams daily, ages 4 to 8 need 25 grams, and ages 9 to 13 need 26 to 31 grams. Most American children consume fewer than 15 grams daily — well below recommendations — making supplementation a practical bridge for fiber-deficient diets.' },
